<br>
Still DKP/Point systems overall have the best chance of success because they are flexible and fair at the same time to avoid possible problems.  Most of the issues that people have w/ the system are once in a life time what ifs that probably are not going to happen, but even though most systems are adapted to handle the situation.  It is the most fair system.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bakxs>Bakxs</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 898<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/13/03 4:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4142.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> God Loot...</span><hr size=1> ...is probably the best overall method--if you have a God who is knowledgable of his players, knowledgable of the game and is fair.  <br>
<br>
Unfortunately there are a lot of selfish, biased and dumb Gods out there.  On the other hand, there are a bunch of good ones too--but I think they are in the minority.  <br>
